# Vercel Build Check Before GitHub Commit/Push

When the user asks to "commit to github", "push to github", or otherwise requests a commit/push workflow:

- Run a production build check first (Vercel-style validation), typically `npm run build` from the project root.
- If the build fails, do not commit/push yet.
- Report the build errors clearly and offer to fix them first.
- Only proceed with commit/push after build passes (or if the user explicitly asks to proceed despite failure).

This rule applies to all commit/push workflows in this project.
